The paper deals with algorithms for counting and sampling subsets, which are fundamental problems in computer science. The use of a tree-based greedy heuristic suggests that the paper may belong to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the heuristic to Bayesian structure discovery in Bayesian networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a tolerance parameter and the guarantee of relative error and total variation distance suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the practical application of the heuristic suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
